item.title: Quiestscape (317)
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

[quote=“CoonHunter, post:18, topic:324505”][quote author=licorish55 link=topic=420902.msg3091418#msg3091418 date=1262917212]

I’ll help you right now.

Find, AutoSpawn.CFG

This isn’t the server help section.

I honestly don’t care.
I’m helping.
As little of members do,

I’m helping by actually telling him.
As in the server help you get.

“Go to Google.com”

“This site is wonderful: Google.com”

People being jerks instead of helping.
[/quote]

Its the fact we dont want people they should feel like they need to ask for everything first to “save time” when, the only way to progress and actually learn how to program, is by learning yourself. I did, and i know alot about 317 servers + clients, so dont say “people being jerks” its actually helping you when you become an adult, because when you grow up, you will learn to either know where it is, or figure it out.[/quote]

I’m sure someone will reply with a “This isn’t a spoonfeeding community” to this, but i’ll say it anyways.

Just because you HAVE to figure it out yourself when you’re a adult, (according to you), doesn’t mean you still can’t ask for help.

Help never hurt, and it helped me learn plenty of times.

I do agree though, you don’t need to ask for help for EVERYTHING, like you said, "It’s the fact we don’t want people they should feel like they need to ask for everything first to “save time”.

Yeah, that might be true, but you need to start somewhere? And when you’re Non-Adult, (because there is NO help in the adult world apparently) you seek your answers and help, in places like this; a learning/teaching and evolving community.

Just because YOU or others, learned on your own, Doesn’t mean everyone else has to…
